4 On my first and only visit to this restaurant I experienced a rare level of genuinely kind and friendly service.   I want to go back for no other reason than the world needs the Blue Fins to keep some remnants of good old service with a smile. When delivered correctly, as Blue Fin does it, you realize that too many places are overdoing it by investing hundreds of thousands of dollars in appearances. This place is a good model for any restaurant owner/manager who is struggling with getting their troops to provide more than sub-par service...  Oh, and I almost forgot about the food. Priced right, tasted fresh, and worth a return trip.
