4 This is a wonderful establishment, and easily the best Japanese fast food restaurant in our city. My review isn't even necessary, as I think the Blue Fin can speak for itself, 99% of the people that come here will leave satisfied. I've found that small dedicated local busineses like this usually engender nothing but respect and praise from their community; but every once in a while you'll get a certain someone who for whatever reason is going to go on the record publicly and trash a place that is beloved by the majority. I wasnt even going to write this review until I saw the egregious 1 star rant that this type of person wrote previously. So, rather than a review proper, this is more of a review coupled with a response to that baffling 1 star atrocity below.  If your the type of person who will shell out 1 and 2 star reviews to mom and pops earnestly trying to serve their community and build a sustainable business, but give 5 star reviews to places like el pollo loco and ross; than please dont come here. you'd be better off in your $15 elastic waste band pants eating greasy chicken in your honda pilot. post script: SEA WEED SALAD IS KING HERE!
4 I'm so glad we have this Asian fast food place on Central Avenue, and near a light rail stop at that. Satisfying, generous fare (love their  sicky rice and the panko dishes!) served by friendly folk; a good number of dishes to choose from; good prices, very informal atmosphere, even a patio for alfresco dining. I feel happy supporting  a local independent business establishment, and even happier that this establishment serves tasty, very filling meals that are not a strain on the budget.
5 My family and I have eaten here at least a hundred times over the years. This is one of two spots we eat lunch at if we are near downtown Phoenix. The price is right and the service is always excellent as is the food. The family who runs the restaurant is always very friendly. I would recommend this place to anyone. My only complaint is that they only have one location in the valley.
4 Review by an "Out-of-towner".......... the SoCal variety.   While this will pretty much "steal my thunder", I must confess that just about everything you could want to know about this little corner fast-food-T-bowl joint is in their website. About the only thing that you won't see would be all the consistent 4 and 5 star reviews from fellow yelpers. You can read those right here on this page.  What drove us to Blue Fin? Driving North from the Chase Stadium district, hungry for a quick lunch before my next appointment, this was the first food place that quickly stood out as a joint that had hot, quick and inexpensive food. Plus... all the street parking in the downtown area near the ball park, and going North for many blocks, have "coin-only" parking meters! Who has rolls of quarters for parking? And doesn't Phoenix know about credit card meters? So we just kept driving North until the frickin' meters disappeared, and we saw this blue corner building with their own parking lot. We pulled in.  The menu is huge. The parking is free. The prices are reasonable, and most orders are brought to your table within five minutes of you ordering and paying at the counter. Enough said; it all works. Oh...... one of the owners spent a few minutes at our table welcoming us to town, and sharing a bit of her family history in Canton, now Kwangchow, China. (Food "and" Entertainment!)
